{
  "texts": [
    "The authors conduct experiments with different open and proprietary LLMs (such as GPT-4, LLaMa) in three settings (answer-only foot_1, chain-of-thought and few-shot settings) to assess how well they perform on SciEval.",
    "In all the settings GPT-4 yields the best results, followed by GPT-3.5-turbo.",
    "Evaluation results show that LLMs do not currently achieve random performance on SciEval's chemistry domain.",
    "All in all, the collected results and system performances demonstrate that if critical thinking is not integrated into classroom methodologies, LLMs and GAI can generate responses and construct answers for a wide range of topics in chemistry with varying quality.",
    "This capability has the potential to influence student performance."
  ]
}